race.comment: OCTA DE LAGO (6) has been ridden quietly then unleashed late in his two runs this prep, the latest over 1250m at the Beaumont track when a few things went wrong but he still got up for second. Lightly raced four-year-old who is cherry ripe for this and looks the goods. HYDROMETER (1) has been racing well in Sydney without threatening. A winner here at this trip from his only try. Very fit and can turn things around in this easier race. EXCEED PERFECTION (8) resumes. Opened last prep with a good second here off a much longer break. Trialling well and should hit the ground running this campaign. TRIPLE TRIPLE (10) led and dug deep to score over 1300m at Taree recently. Faces some better types today but can give some cheek. DEPUTIZE (5) is back from a ten-month absence. Absolutely bolted in when fresh from a spell at the Sunshine Coast last prep. Must come under consideration.
